'''Robin Hranáč''' ({{IPA|cs|ˈɦranaːt͡ʃ}}, born 29 January 2000) is a Czech professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Club career==
Hranáč started his professional career at [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]], making his [[Czech First League]] debut against [[FK Teplice|Teplice]] in April 2021. In the summer of that year, Hranáč joined [[Slovak Super Liga|Fortuna Liga]] side [[MFK Tatran Liptovský Mikuláš|Tatran Liptovský Mikuláš]] on loan, playing the full length of the club's first 13 games before receiving a red card against [[FC Spartak Trnava|Spartak Trnava]].<ref name="u21callup">{{Cite web|url=https://plzensky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/hranac-se-pod-tatrami-rozehral-a-ted-muze-v-anglii-poprve-nastoupit-za-repre-202.html|title=Hranáč se pod Tatrami rozehrál. A teď může v Anglii poprvé nastoupit za repre|language=cs|work=[[Deník]]|first=Zdeněk|last=Soukup|date=11 November 2021|access-date=6 May 2025}}</ref>

He played 39 matches for [[FK Pardubice|Pardubice]] across a year and a half of loans from early 2022 until the end of the 2023–24 season. After returning to his parent club, Viktoria Plzeň, Hranáč broke into the first team and featured regularly during the Czech First League as well as the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa Conference League]], in which his side reached the quarter-finals.<ref name="objev-sezony">{{Cite web|title=Plzeň řeší nabídky na Hranáče. Objev sezony má blízko do Hoffenheimu|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/robin-hranac-viktoria-plzen-hoffenheim-prestup.A240823_155803_fotbal_min|first=Miloslav|last=Novák|website=idnes.cz|date=23 August 2024|access-date=6 May 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

On 25 August 2024, Hranáč signed a multi-year contract with [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]], for a fee reported to be up to 11 million Euros. It was announced concurrently that he would wear the number 2 shirt for the club.<ref name="signed-hoffenheim">{{Cite web|title=Čtvrtý Čech v Hoffenheimu. Hranáč dostal v Německu dlouhodobý kontrakt|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/zahranici/robin-hranac-viktoria-plzen-hoffenheim.A240825_101329_fot_zahranici_jic|first=Jiří|last=Čihák|website=idnes.cz|date=25 August 2024|access-date=6 May 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
Hranáč received his first call-up to the [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team]] in 2021 ahead of matches against [[England national under-21 football team|England]] and [[Slovenia national under-21 football team|Slovenia]].<ref name="u21callup"/> He represented the Czech Republic at the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=Israel U21 v Czech Republic U21 game report|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036142/|website=UEFA|date=28 June 2023}}</ref>

His first call-up for the senior [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]] came in spring 2024.<ref name="signed-hoffenheim"/> He made his debut in a [[Exhibition match#Association football|friendly match]] against Armenia on 26 March 2024.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Filip|last=Ardon|title=Češi otáčeli vývoj i na Letné. Výhru nad Arménií zařídil střídající Chorý|url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal/cesko-armenie-fotbal-priprava-hasek.html|website=[[Deník]]|publisher=Vltava Labe Media|date=26 March 2024|language=cs|quote=Debutu se pak dočkali brankář Matěj Kovář a obránci Adam Gabriel, Robin Hranáč a Tomáš Vlček.|trans-quote=Goalkeeper Matěj Kovář and defenders Adam Gabriel, Robin Hranáč and Tomáš Vlček debut.}}</ref> Hranáč played all three of his nation's matches at [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref name="objev-sezony"/>

